All Implemented Interfaces:
IDInterface
public class Occurrence
extends Statement

Occurrences are a Connectable's links to the 'outer world'. An occurrence is a representation of a relationship between a Connectable and an information resource. Occurrences always have an OccurType - every Occurrence of the same nature references the same OccurType. Every Occurrence is attached to exactly one Connectable.

Author:
Matthias
